question: Question_05
statement:
When a person breathes, the volume of air in the lungs may be modelled
by a function of the form

\[\displaystyle
V(t) = C + A\sin(\omega t + \phi),\] where \emph{V} is the volume in
millilitres and \emph{t} is time in seconds. Suppose the minimum and
maximum volumes are 1400 and 3400 ml respectively, and the maximum rate
of change of \emph{V} is 1200 ml/sec.

What is the period of \emph{V}(\emph{t})?
